article.headline: Allison's 20 points helps Baylor breeze past SE Missouri
article.linkText: Balanced effort helps No. 11 Baylor cruise to win
article.story:
CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) --  Rachel Allison had 20 points and 10 rebounds to lead Baylor (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 10 AP) to an 81-51 win over Southeast Missouri on Thursday night.

Danielle Wilson had 12 points and 12 rebounds and Jhasmin Player had 13 points and 10 assists for the Bears (6-0). Angela Tisdale added 18 points.

Tarina Nixon led Southeast Missouri (4-3) with 15 points. Sonya Daugherty added 12.

Baylor, which has outscored its first six opponents by an average of nearly 36 points, outrebounded Southeast Missouri 52-20, including a 29-7 edge in the first half.

Baylor shot 55.6 percent from the field, while Southeast Missouri made just 31.6 percent of its field goals. The Redhawks made 6 of 9 3-pointers in the second half.
